causing that events from this integration won\'t be triggered. There are 2 ways to fix this issue:\r\n\r\n1) On the form(s) you want to trigger events you need to activate the subscribers-only mode:\r\nContact Form -> Additional Settings -> subscribers_only: true\r\n\r\n2) Enable the subscribers-only mode to all forms placing the following code on your <code>functions.php</code>: \r\n<code>add_filter( \'wpcf7_verify_nonce\', \'__return_true\' );</code>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://contactform7.com/2017/08/18/contact-form-7-49/\">Official post</a> about subscribers-only mode from the Contact Form 7 team.\r\n\r\nImportant: Forms with subscribers-only mode to will require to your users to stay logged in to be able to submit the form, it means that visitors can\'t submit the form.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:37:\"Connect GamiPress with Contact Form 7\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:67:\"https://gamipress.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/contact-form-7.svg\";s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:23;s:4:\"name\";s:4:\"Form\";s:4:\"slug\";s:4:\"form\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:23;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:17:\"download_category\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:7;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:36;s:4:\"name\";s:4:\"Free\";s:4:\"slug\";s:4:\"free\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:36;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:17:\"download_category\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:63;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":10:{s:7:\"term_id\";i:40;s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Integrations\";s:4:\"slug\";s:12:\"integrations\";s:10:\"term_group\";i:0;s:16:\"term_taxonomy_id\";i:40;s:8:\"taxonomy\";s:17:\"download_category\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"parent\";i:0;s:5:\"count\";i:52;s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}}s:4:\"tags\";b:0;}s:7:\"pricing\";O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:6:\"amount\";s:4:\"0.00\";}s:9:\"licensing\";O:8:\"stdClass\"